      .span6
        .headshot.pull-left
          %img{:src => "/ab_theme/img/crd-headshot.png", :alt => "CRD Thumbnail"}
        %p
          My first exposure to a programming language was in elementary school (er, back in a decade that rhymes with "ladies"), where I used LOGO to create elaborate turtle art on green-monochrome Apple IIe's and Commodore 64s ('Load "*", 8, 1' anyone?).
        %p
          Later, high school brought with it PCs, 9600 baud modems, BBSes, and Pascal.  A liberal arts degree and career in advertising meant I largely missed Visual Basic, Java, and PHP, and it wasn't until 2010 that I opened up a text editor and taught myself HTML & CSS.
        %p
          In the fall of 2011, I took General Assembly's 10-week Front End Web Developent Course.  I've since recommended the course to others and I think it's an amazing way to get up-to-speed on HTML, CSS, and Javascript in a relatively short amount of time.
        %p
          Finally, in February of 2012 I enrolled in Avi Flombaum's' 8-week Ruby on Rails intensive.  This, along with Michael Hartl's online tutorial, was enough to get me off the ground and building (simple) web apps.
        %p
          Since then, I've been working on a handful of personal projects (see above), and, as Jesse Farmer of Dev Bootcamp says, I try hard to 
